      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAJOR ACE (1) had to overcome a collision with another runner and could manage only a distant fourth (23.09) in a Grade 4/5 over 400m at this track. Better than latest and worth another try. RIGATONI MONELLI (2) tends to take a while to wind up, missing the placings two back but running on to last time finishing second (22.67) in a Grade 4/5 at this track. Has a good record at this journey. Form is hard to fault from this box, with a win and two minor placings from three starts. Expected to be in the finish again. TORINO (8) should get a clear run from the wide draw. Safely held last start when a 17 length 8th at Cannington (31.28). Form here at this distance is strong including six wins. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Bold showing expected. MAXIMUM HUGHES (6) has a solid strike rate at this track and distance.",
